Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getSchedulingFile(25.10)                              getSchedulingFile(25.10)

Name
       getSchedulingFile

Syntax
       getSchedulingFile

       [-help]

       Returns  the  name of the current scheduling file used by the skewClock
       command. If no scheduling file name is set,  getSchedulingFile  returns
       nothing.  If  you  have already run skewClock, this command reports the
       default file name. If you have specified or changed the scheduling file
       name using setSchedulingFile, then this command returns this name.

       To view the above description in the software, use  man  getScheduling-
       File.

Related Information
